HEADWORD: Frustule
<hw>Frus"tule</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>frustulum</ets>, dim. fr. <ets>frustum</ets> a piece: cf. F.
<ets>frustule</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>The siliceous shell
of a diatom. It is composed of two valves, one overlapping the other,
like a pill box and its cover.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Frustulent</ent>⟦br⟧
